# frontend-architecture

## Component Hierarchy

### Faction System Components
- `components/factions/FactionGrid.tsx`: Hexagonal grid layout for displaying 7 unique factions with connection lines indicating technological relationships
- `components/factions/FactionCard.tsx`: Faction-specific cards with dynamic theming and visual effects based on faction technology 
- `components/factions/TimelineSection.tsx`: Tracks faction emergence and technological development across three possible future paths

### Game Interface Components
- `features/battlefield/Battlefield.tsx`: Grid-based combat system with distinct zones and faction-specific rules
- `features/battlefield/TurnManager.tsx`: Three-phase turn structure with resource management
- `features/cards/CardHand.tsx`: Hand management with faction-specific card interactions

### Deck Building Components 
- `components/deck-builder/DeckBuilder.tsx`: Implements complex deck building rules:
  - Maximum 3 copies per card (1 for Hero cards)
  - 30-50 cards per deck
  - Maximum 2 factions per deck
  - Hero card requirements
  - Faction consistency validation

### State Management
- Faction state: Manages active faction themes, technology levels, and integration paths
- Game state: Tracks battlefield state, turn phases, and resource systems (Energy/Momentum)
- Collection state: Manages card ownership, deck compositions, and faction progression

### UI/UX Implementation
- Dynamic faction theming system adapting colors, effects, and animations
- Hexagonal grid layout system for faction relationships
- Responsive battlefield grid with zone-specific rules
- Interactive card preview and detail system
- Real-time resource and state tracking displays

